kturen sind geschaffen worden? Und ist es moglich, aus den finnischen Erfahrungen Empfehlungen fur Lander wie Deutschland abzuleiten?  aFinland is the undisputed pioneer in architectural education. In 1998, it was one of the first countries in Europe to develop an official architectural policy, the declared aim of which was to more systematically integrate architecture into the educational system, teacher training programs at universities, and adult education. In her field study, Turit Frobe spoke with various experts to get a picture of just how successful this internationally acclaimed Finnish architectural policy has been. Has it succeeded in anchoring architectural education in the education system? What conditions did this require? What structures were created to do so? And is it possible to derive recommendations from Finnish experience for countries such as Germany?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aArchitecture and statezFinland. 0aArchitecturexStudy and teachingzFinland. 4aadult education. 4aarchitectural education. 4aarchitectural policy. 4aeducational system. 4ateacher training. 4auniversities. 7aARCHITECTURE / Regional.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG0 cprintz978386859616840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978386859938140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783868599381423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783868599381/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  a978-3-11-069628-8 